==Abstract==

This IIP describes the "mempool" P2P message which requests a peer to send inv messages for all transactions in their mempool. It is adapted from BIP 35 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

The mempool message enables:

* Wallet synchronization without full blockchain rescan
* Lightweight client transaction awareness
* Mempool synchronization between nodes

==Specification==

===Message Format===

The "mempool" message has no payload:

<pre>
mempool message: (empty)
</pre>

===Response===

Upon receiving a mempool message, a node SHOULD respond with one or more "inv" messages containing the txids of all transactions in its mempool.

<pre>
inv message:
  count: varint
  inventory: [
    { type: MSG_TX (1), hash: txid },
    ...
  ]
</pre>

===Rate Limiting===

Nodes MAY rate-limit mempool requests to prevent DoS attacks:
* Maximum 1 mempool request per connection per 60 seconds
* Peers violating limits may be disconnected

===Permission===

Nodes MAY require the "mempool" permission (via -whitelist) to respond to mempool requests.

==Rationale==

The mempool message provides a simple mechanism for transaction discovery without the complexity of bloom filters (IIP-11).

